GENERAL

'rpass' is a module and related executable that are meant to make secure password management through the commandline accessible, convenient, and easy.

USAGE

The command 'rpass' on its own will list account names and corresponding fields.
The command 'rpass' followed by any text will print any accounts that contain the text, case-insensitive (regular expressions allowed).
The command 'rpass -a' brings up an interface to add accounts and information.
See rpass -h for more information.

After installation, the module can be imported with 'import rpass'.

DEPENDENCIES

The executable 'gpg' must be in your $PATH.
